          "reviewRating": {
            "@type": "Rating",
            "ratingValue": "5",
            "bestRating": "5",
            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "Thanks to internet, i found this school for my kid in 2021. Total lockdown, secod wave and we had no option to visit any school. I called Vels, admission staff, the head everyone talked to me so nicely and answered all my questions and doubts. Teachers in grade 2 are amazing, qualified and so kind to each kid. Teachers give time to every kid and god know how nicely they manage to do it in 45 mins. Less screen time.. less homework...happy kids...\ncnt say abt school infra.. i didnot visit yet but it does not mtr as long as teachers are great.",
          "publisher": {
            "@type": "Organization",
            "name": "Yellow Slate"
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Review",
          "itemReviewed": {
            "@type": "School",
            "name": "Vels International Preschool - Neelankarai"
          },
          "author": {
            "@type": "Person",
            "name": "Manashi Chakraborty"
          },
          "datePublished": "2021-03-22",
          "reviewRating": {
            "@type": "Rating",
            "ratingValue": "5",
            "bestRating": "5",
            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "Salute to TEACHERS , Backbone of our Country, Pillars of A Civilised Society.\nReview regarding School at Home\n\nI am surprised the way teachers taught each and every topics in class minutely through the newest medium of Teaching-Learning Process.\n\nI never felt that this topic from this subject could be explained better if kids would have been at school.\n\nMy daughter is highly influenced by teachers, rather i would say me and my husband enjoy our journey again back to school. we can commemorate , we can re-learn basic values of our life what we have learnt in our own school.\n\nThis journey of Teaching-Learning, was an excellent experience for Parents, Grand-parents who attended class together with their child at home.\n\nThank you All again 😀🙏🙏🙏\n\nI heard lot of parents from lot of other schools are having hundreds of problems during this School From Home period.\n\nWe had no issues regarding Vels International Preschool.\n\nWe have no glitches regarding VELS International Preschool.",
